R Notebook

library(readxl)
library(xlsx)
library(sjPlot)
library(ggplot2)
library(lme4)
## Loading required package: Matrix
library(stringr)
library(ggExtra)
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
# linguistic data
if (rstudioapi::isAvailable()){
  currdir = dirname(rstudioapi::getSourceEditorContext()$path)
} else {
  currdir = getwd()
}
file_path = file.path(dirname(dirname(currdir)), 'data/extracted_align_data_2.xlsx')
data <- read_excel(file_path)
# Handling data
data$Agent = ifelse(data$conv == 1,"H","R")
data = data[!(data$locutor %in% c(1,4,19,23)),]
# Adding / renaming columns
data$Trial = data$conv_id_unif
## Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `conv_id_unif`.
data$Trial2 = paste0('t', str_pad(data$Trial, 2, pad = "0"))
## Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `Trial`.
# Creating dfs
data_convprime = data[which(data$prime == "conversant"),]
data_partprime = data[which(data$prime == "participant"),]
# extra columns will add themselves automatically - just creating structures
df_overall = data.frame(mean=numeric(2),
                std=numeric(2), 
                mean_r=numeric(2),
                std_r=numeric(2),
                mean_h=numeric(2),
                std_h=numeric(2),
                row.names = c('lilla_conv','lilla_part'),
                stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

lilla convprime

ggplot(data_convprime, aes(x = lilla, color=Agent)) + geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..), alpha=0.5, fill="white") + geom_density(alpha=.2)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

ggplot(data_convprime, aes(x = Trial2, y = lilla, color=Agent)) + geom_boxplot()

ggplot(data_convprime, 
       aes(x = Agent,
           fill = Agent,  
           y = lilla)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = mean,
               geom = "bar") +
  stat_summary(fun.ymin = function(x) mean(x) - sd(x), 
               fun.ymax = function(x) mean(x) + sd(x), 
               geom="errorbar", 
               width = 0.25) +
  labs(x = "Agent",
       y = 'lilla')

# applying mixed model
mdl = lmer('lilla ~ Agent * Trial + (1 | locutor)', data = data_convprime)
## Error in eval(predvars, data, env): object 'Trial' not found
print(summary(mdl))
## Error in summary(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
tab_model(mdl, title = 'lilla')
## Error in tab_model(mdl, title = "lilla"): object 'mdl' not found
#print(confint(mdl))

# saving data
s = summary(mdl)[['coefficients']]
## Error in summary(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
s = data.frame(s)
## Error in data.frame(s): object 's' not found
s$Feature = 'lilla_conv'
## Error in s$Feature = "lilla_conv": object 's' not found
l = data.frame(confint(mdl))[3:6,]
## Error in confint(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
df_model = cbind(s,l)
## Error in cbind(s, l): object 's' not found
# saving other features
data_r = data_convprime[which(data_convprime$Agent == "R"),]
data_h = data_convprime[which(data_convprime$Agent == "H"),]
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'mean'] = mean(data$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'std'] = sd(data$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'mean_r'] = mean(data_r$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'std_r'] = sd(data_r$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'mean_h'] = mean(data_h$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_conv', 'std_h'] = sd(data_h$'lilla')

lilla partprime

ggplot(data_partprime, aes(x = lilla, color=Agent)) + geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..), alpha=0.5, fill="white") + geom_density(alpha=.2)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

ggplot(data_partprime, aes(x = Trial2, y = lilla, color=Agent)) + geom_boxplot()

ggplot(data_partprime, 
       aes(x = Agent,
           fill = Agent,  
           y = lilla)) +
  stat_summary(fun.y = mean,
               geom = "bar") +
  stat_summary(fun.ymin = function(x) mean(x) - sd(x), 
               fun.ymax = function(x) mean(x) + sd(x), 
               geom="errorbar", 
               width = 0.25) +
  labs(x = "Agent",
       y = 'lilla')

# applying mixed model
mdl = lmer('lilla ~ Agent * Trial + (1 | locutor)', data = data_partprime)
## Error in eval(predvars, data, env): object 'Trial' not found
print(summary(mdl))
## Error in summary(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
tab_model(mdl, title = 'lilla')
## Error in tab_model(mdl, title = "lilla"): object 'mdl' not found
#print(confint(mdl))

# saving data
s = summary(mdl)[['coefficients']]
## Error in summary(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
s = data.frame(s)
## Error in data.frame(s): object 's' not found
s$Feature = 'lilla_part'
## Error in s$Feature = "lilla_part": object 's' not found
l = data.frame(confint(mdl))[3:6,]
## Error in confint(mdl): object 'mdl' not found
df_model = rbind(df_model, cbind(s,l))
## Error in rbind(df_model, cbind(s, l)): object 'df_model' not found
# saving other features
data_r = data_partprime[which(data_partprime$Agent == "R"),]
data_h = data_partprime[which(data_partprime$Agent == "H"),]
df_overall['lilla_part', 'mean'] = mean(data$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_part', 'std'] = sd(data$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_part', 'mean_r'] = mean(data_r$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_part', 'std_r'] = sd(data_r$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_part', 'mean_h'] = mean(data_h$'lilla')
df_overall['lilla_part', 'std_h'] = sd(data_h$'lilla')
names(data_convprime)[names(data_convprime) == 'lilla'] = 'data_conv'
names(data_partprime)[names(data_partprime) == 'lilla'] = 'data_part'
merres = merge(data_convprime[,c('locutor', "Trial", "Agent", 'data_conv')], data_partprime[,c('locutor', "Trial", "Agent", 'data_part')], by=c("locutor", "Trial", "Agent"))
## Error: Can't subset columns that don't exist.
## [31mx[39m The column `Trial` doesn't exist.
# plot
g <- ggplot(merres, aes(x = data_conv, y = data_part, color=Agent)) + 
        geom_point(alpha = 0.7) + 
        geom_density_2d(alpha=0.5) + 
        theme(legend.position="bottom") + xlim(0,max(merres$data_conv)) + ylim(0,max(merres$data_part)) +
        labs(x = "VI: lilla conv",
            y = "VD: lilla part",
            color = "Agent")
## Error in ggplot(merres, aes(x = data_conv, y = data_part, color = Agent)): object 'merres' not found
ggMarginal(g, type="densigram", margins = "both", groupColour = TRUE, fill="white")
## Error in reconcileScatPlot(p, data, x, y): object 'g' not found
# change names to avoid later confusion
names(data_convprime)[names(data_convprime) == 'data_conv'] = 'lilla' 
names(data_partprime)[names(data_partprime) == 'data_part'] = 'lilla'

Saver

if (rstudioapi::isAvailable()){
  file_path = file.path(dirname(rstudioapi::getSourceEditorContext()$path), 'summary_align.xlsx')
} else {
  file_path = file.path(getwd(), 'summary_align.xlsx')
}
# Write the first data set in a new workbook
write.xlsx(df_overall, file = file_path,
      sheetName = 'summary', append = FALSE)
# Write others sheets

write.xlsx(df_model, file = file_path,
      sheetName = 'model', append = TRUE)
